Looking for an endgame where Whites King can't cover the Kingside and Queenside simultaneously. I was very aware, and afraid of the potential negative effects, of Whites ability to dislodge the Knight with e3-e4. I also thought about the pawn structure weakness for White that would come with e3-e4.

Continuously working toward a Queenside that required Whites Kings assistance. At this point in time, I thought there would be a game of cat-and-mouse between Blacks Knight and Rook, and Whites Bishop, Rook, and King. I didn't know who would win that battle, and didn't know if Black would be able to take control of the Kingside as a result of it.
